1 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 8206 of Title 62, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The Office of Management and Enterprise Services shall
5 promulgate all necessary rules for the administration of this act
6 within the time prescribed for permanent rule adoption as provided
7 by law.
8 SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 8207 of Title 62, unless there
10 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 The database shall be hosted and featured prominently on a
12 website owned or controlled by the Office of Management and
13 Enterprise Services for purposes of allowing the display of
14 information required by this act. The Submitting Party shall
15 display on its website a prominent Internet link to a page within
16 the database that displays a summary of the expenditures from the
17 Submitting Party in the most recent fiscal year.
18 SECTION 8. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
